# Trivy vulnerability ignore file
# Add CVE IDs here to suppress known false positives, e.g.:
# CVE-2023-XXXXX

# ============================================================
# Go stdlib CVEs in the esbuild binary
# ============================================================
# These CVEs are in the compiled Go binary embedded inside the
# esbuild npm package (drizzle-kit → @esbuild-kit/core-utils → @esbuild/linux-x64/bin/esbuild).
# esbuild is a CLI build tool — it is never run as a network server in production.
# All network/TLS/crypto attack vectors are therefore NOT exploitable.
# The real fix would be to run drizzle migrations outside the app image;
# for now these are accepted as non-exploitable in this deployment context.

